    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-10-04T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-10-04T16:00:00-05:00" n="774"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d774">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/1541: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Long</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-04T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 4, 1935—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>154. Chargé d’Affaires at Addis Ababa reports that he has advised all American
                    institutions to paint or stretch large American flags on roofs of their
                    buildings and that he is doing the same at the Legation, which is at the
                    opposite end of the city from other foreign legations. At present the Chargé
                    d’Affaires, along with numerous other American citizens, is living at the
                    Imperial Hotel. The location of the American legation, American institutions and
                    the Imperial Hotel is readily ascertainable from existing maps.</p>
                <p>Please express to the Foreign Office the hope that Italian military authorities
                    in East Africa may be advised of the foregoing for use in the event of military
                    operations at or near Addis Ababa.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
